name: {{LOOP_NAME}}
description: >
  A cargo-test-gated bounded loop, scaffolded via `bl new cargo-test-basic`.
pattern: evaluator-optimizer
role: [backend]
rung: L2
spec: PROMPT.md
runner:
  default: stub
gate:
  kind: command
  # CommandGate's expected_fail_codes defaults to {1} and gate.kind=command
  # does not forward extra gate.* keys to the constructor (composition.py),
  # so a normal gate-fail MUST exit 1. `cargo test` exits 101 on any test
  # failure (and on a compile error — cargo has no pytest-style separate
  # exit code for that), so the `|| exit 1` normalizes cargo's 101 down to
  # the 1 CommandGate expects. This deliberately treats "won't compile" the
  # same as "compiles but a test fails" — both are a normal gate-fail here,
  # not a GateError, matching cargo's own single-exit-code contract.
  run: "cd seed && cargo test -q || exit 1"
bounds: bounds.yaml
memory: STATE.md
